# ITops Agent — Cursor 入口文件
# 创建于 2026-07-21（v2 报告 §9.2 P1-#21）
# 完整规则见 AGENTS.md（如有冲突，以 AGENTS.md 为准）

ITops Agent is a one-stop intelligent ops platform.
Stack: Node.js + Express + TypeScript + SQLite (backend) / React + Vite + Ant Design + Tailwind (frontend).
DDD modules: 24 backend modules + 23 frontend modules. See `.trae/rules/architecture.md` §1.2.

## 5 Iron Rules (请严格遵守)

1. **Layered dependency, single direction**: core/ → modules/ → routes/. Never invert.
   - Allowed: Module A/services → Module B/services (via service layer)
   - Allowed: modules/<m>/services → repositories/
   - Forbidden: repositories/ → modules/
   - Forbidden: core/ → modules/
   - Forbidden: Module A/routes → Module B/routes
   - Forbidden: modules/<m>/routes → repositories/ (ADR-016)

2. **Routes layer does only 3 things**:
   - (1) Parameter validation (Zod)
   - (1.5) Auth check (requireRole)
   - (2) Call service
   - (3) Return response
   - Never write business logic in routes. Never import repositories directly. Never call utility functions without going through service.

3. **New files must be ≤ 500 lines (excluding comments/blanks)**. If a new file would exceed 500 lines, split it into subdirectories/sub-components. See `frontend/src/modules/ai/pages/agents/tool/` for a 4-file split example.

4. **Don't write test files unless explicitly asked**. The project is in exploration phase; tests are written on demand. Existing tests concentrate in services/ and repositories/.

5. **All reports/plans go to `docs/`**. All ADRs go to `.trae/adr/NNN-<slug>.md` (numbered, see `.trae/adr/README.md`).

## Naming Conventions

| Object | Naming | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Tools/Services | camelCase | `agentToolRegistry` |
| Classes/Interfaces | PascalCase | `AgentTool`, `ToolCallContext` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE | `MCP_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE` |
| Filenames | camelCase.ts | `agentCrudService.ts` |
| DB tables/columns | snake_case | `audit_logs`, `user_id` |
| HTTP paths | kebab-case | `/api/v1/agents/tools` |

## Ubiquitous Language (do not use aliases)

| Concept | ✅ Use | ❌ Don't use |
|---|---|---|
| Alert | alert | ~~alarm~~ |
| Work item | task | ~~job~~ |
| Process chain | workflow | ~~pipeline~~ |
| Message | notification | ~~notice~~ |
| Sign-off | approval | ~~review~~ |
| Auto fix | remediation | ~~fix~~ |
| AI worker | agent | ~~bot~~ |

## Directory Layout

backend/src/
├── core/                    # DI container (infra layer)
├── middleware/              # auth/errorHandler/rateLimiter/trace/validation
├── repositories/            # Data access (28 .ts + 11 subdirs, only via this layer)
├── shared/schemas/          # Zod validation (apiValidation.ts central)
├── modules/<name>/
│   ├── routes/              # Thin routes
│   ├── services/            # Thick business logic
│   ├── repositories/        # Module-private repos (optional)
│   └── README.md            # Required
└── app.ts

frontend/src/modules/<name>/
├── routes.ts                # React.lazy routes
├── api.ts                   # API wrapper
├── index.ts                 # barrel export
├── pages/                   # Page components
└── README.md                # Required

## Quality Gates

- TypeScript strict mode: `npm run tsc --noEmit` must show 0 errors
- ESLint: `npm run lint` should pass (0 errors). `no-any` is enforced.
- Architecture: `npx depcruise --config .dependency-cruiser.json backend/src`
- Tests: vitest, see `backend/vitest.config.ts` for thresholds

## Common Anti-Patterns (avoid these!)

| ❌ Wrong | ✅ Right |
|---|---|
| Business if/else in routes | Move to service layer |
| `import { repo } from '../../repositories'` in routes | `import { xxxService } from '../services/xxxCrudService'` |
| `const result: any = await api.get(...)` | `const { data } = await api.get<MyType>(...)` |
| `localStorage.getItem('token')` | `useAuth()` from `@/contexts/AuthContext` |
| New file 800 lines un-split | Split per the `tool/` example |
| Modify `migrations/v001_*.ts` SQL | Create `v0XX_*.ts` instead |
| Read+modify .trae/rules/ silently | **Must report to user** (see `.trae/rules/top-rules.md`) |
| `process.env.SOMETHING` | Use settings table, manage from /settings page |

## Workflow on New Task

1. Read this file (you're reading it)
2. Read relevant module's README.md
3. Look at existing code in the same module as a template
4. Decide which module the task belongs to
5. Read only relevant code, don't blindly read everything
6. New files must obey the 5 iron rules above
7. After changes: run lint + tsc

